The paper proposes a novel multi-task learning method for personalized attribute preference prediction, which involves understanding and predicting personalized annotations. This task is relevant to several sub-fields of computer science, including machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), natural language processing (cs.CL), and information retrieval (cs.IR). Given the focus on developing a new optimization method and providing theoretical guarantees, cs.LG is the most likely sub-category, followed by cs.CV and cs.AI. However, the paper also discusses the use of textual annotations, which suggests relevance to cs.CL and cs.IR.
